TransferResult.Explanation: In PostgreSQL, the ROUND function can also take a second argument to specify the number of decimal places to round to, similar to DuckDB. However, to ensure that the first argument is treated as a numeric type, I cast it using '::numeric'. This maintains the semantics of the original DuckDB statement while adhering to the requirements of not introducing meaningless features or random return values.

MutateResult: SELECT ROUND(0.1::numeric, 1000) FROM pg_catalog.pg_namespace WHERE pg_catalog.pg_namespace.oid UNION ALL SELECT ROUND(0.1::numeric, 1000) FROM pg_catalog.pg_namespace WHERE NOT (pg_catalog.pg_namespace.oid) UNION ALL SELECT ROUND(0.1::numeric, 1000) FROM pg_catalog.pg_namespace WHERE (pg_catalog.pg_namespace.oid) IS NULL;
